*Most of the content of this page is historic. As of [NetHack 3.6.7](/wiki/NetHack_3.6.7 "NetHack 3.6.7"), only BOULDER and WARNINGS are still accepted. See [Custom map symbols](/wiki/Custom_map_symbols "Custom map symbols") for equivalent features in 3.6.7.*

The [NetHack 3.4.3](/wiki/NetHack_3.4.3 "NetHack 3.4.3") configuration file (.nethackrc on [Unix](/wiki/Unix "Unix"), defaults.nh on [MS-DOS](/wiki/MS-DOS "MS-DOS") and [Windows](/wiki/Windows "Windows") including Windows CE, NetHack Defaults on [Mac](/wiki/Mac "Mac") and [BeOS](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BeOS "wikipedia:BeOS"), and NetHack.cnf on [Amiga](/wiki/Amiga "Amiga"), [Atari](/wiki/Atari "Atari"), [OS/2](/wiki/OS/2 "OS/2") and [VMS](/wiki/VMS "VMS")) provides several options to set **custom map symbols**.

## The options

The options take the form VARIABLE = number number number.... They are shown here in the form that gives the default [IBMgraphics](/wiki/IBMgraphics "IBMgraphics") symbols when [code page 437](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/code_page_437 "wikipedia:code page 437") is set.

### BOULDER

This option takes one number, to set the symbol for a boulder:

```
BOULDER = 039
```

The default appearance is `` ` ``. This can also be set using `` OPTIONS=boulder:` ``.

### GRAPHICS *(historic)*

This option takes 92 numbers, to set the symbols for all fixed parts of the dungeon and certain special effects; that is, all symbols except for monsters and objects:

           040 048 035 064 042 047 045 092 179 179 \
           092 045 047 047 045 092 179 032 179 092 \

### DUNGEON *(historic)*

This option takes 41 numbers, to set the symbols for all fixed parts of the dungeon except for traps:

```
DUNGEON = 032 179 196 218 191 192 217 197 193 194 \
          180 195 250 254 254 043 043 240 241 250 \
          176 177 060 062 060 062 095 124 092 035 \
          244 247 250 247 250 250 035 035 032 035 \
          247
```

These are the same as the first 41 numbers in GRAPHICS; consequently, if you set GRAPHICS, you do not need to set DUNGEON.

The configuration file has a commented-out version of DUNGEON that is claimed to set the default IBMgraphics; in fact, it differs from the above in that it sets stairs to 243 and 242, appearing as ≤ and ≥.

Custom map symbols (3.4.3)

From NetHackWiki
Jump to navigation Jump to search

Most of the content of this page is historic. As of NetHack 3.6.7, only BOULDER and WARNINGS are still accepted. See Custom map symbols for equivalent features in 3.6.7.

The NetHack 3.4.3 configuration file (.nethackrc on Unix, defaults.nh on MS-DOS and Windows including Windows CE, NetHack Defaults on Mac and BeOS, and NetHack.cnf on Amiga, Atari, OS/2 and VMS) provides several options to set custom map symbols.

The options

The options take the form VARIABLE = number number number.... They are shown here in the form that gives the default IBMgraphics symbols when code page 437 is set.

BOULDER

This option takes one number, to set the symbol for a boulder: 

BOULDER = 039

The default appearance is `. This can also be set using OPTIONS=boulder:`.

''Most of the content of this page is historic. As of [[NetHack 3.6.7]], only BOULDER and WARNINGS are still accepted. See [[Custom map symbols]] for equivalent features in 3.6.7.''

The [[NetHack 3.4.3]] configuration file (.nethackrc on [[Unix]], defaults.nh on [[MS-DOS]] and [[Windows]] including Windows CE, NetHack Defaults on [[Mac]] and [[wikipedia:BeOS|BeOS]], and NetHack.cnf on [[Amiga]], [[Atari]], [[OS/2]] and [[VMS]]) provides several options to set '''custom map symbols'''.

== The options ==

The options take the form VARIABLE = number number number....  They are shown here in the form that gives the default [[IBMgraphics]] symbols when [[wikipedia:code page 437|code page 437]] is set.

=== BOULDER ===

This option takes one number, to set the symbol for a boulder:

 BOULDER = 039

The default appearance is <tt>`</tt>.  This can also be set using <tt>OPTIONS=boulder:`</tt>.
